---
description: Enforce backend route API contract naming and schema conventions
globs: src/server/lib/routes/**/*.ts
alwaysApply: true
---

# Route API Contracts Rule

Apply this rule whenever creating or editing backend routes under `src/server/lib/routes`.

## Endpoint directory contract

Each endpoint directory must include:

- `<endpoint-name>.route.ts`
- `<endpoint-name>.config.ts`
- `<endpoint-name>.handler.ts`
- `index.ts`
- `schemas/index.ts` and explicit `*.schema.ts` files as needed

### Valid

- `src/server/lib/routes/video/get-token/get-token.config.ts`
- `src/server/lib/routes/video/get-token/get-token.handler.ts`
- `src/server/lib/routes/video/get-token/get-token.route.ts`
- `src/server/lib/routes/video/get-token/schemas/body.schema.ts`
- `src/server/lib/routes/video/get-token/schemas/response.schema.ts`

### Invalid

- `src/server/lib/routes/video/get-token/config.ts` (missing endpoint prefix)
- `src/server/lib/routes/video/get-token/handler.ts` (missing endpoint prefix)
- `src/server/lib/routes/video/get-token/schemas/get-token.schemas.ts` (plural schema filename)

## Symbol naming contract

For endpoint directory `<endpoint-name>` (kebab-case):

- export `<endpointName>Config` from config file
- export `<endpointName>Handler` from handler file
- export `<endpointName>Router` from route file

### Valid

```ts
export const getTokenConfig = createRoute(...);
export const getTokenHandler: RouteHandler<...> = async (c) => { ... };
export const getTokenRouter = new OpenAPIHono<{ Bindings: Env }>();
```

### Invalid

```ts
export const config = createRoute(...);
export const handler = async (c) => { ... };
export const router = new OpenAPIHono();
```

## Schema naming contract

Use singular schema filenames only:

- `body.schema.ts`
- `query.schema.ts`
- `params.schema.ts`
- `response.schema.ts`
- `error.schema.ts`

Never create:

- `*.schemas.ts`

### Valid

- `schemas/body.schema.ts`
- `schemas/error.schema.ts`

### Invalid

- `schemas/body.schemas.ts`
- `schemas/errors.schemas.ts`

## Schema coverage expectations

For every endpoint:

- define explicit success response schema
- define explicit error schema if endpoint documents error responses
- keep `schemas/index.ts` as re-export-only barrel

### Valid

```ts
// schemas/index.ts
export { MyBodySchema, type MyBody } from './body.schema';
export { MyResponseSchema, type MyResponse } from './response.schema';
export { MyErrorSchema, type MyError } from './error.schema';
```

### Invalid

```ts
// schemas/index.ts
import { z } from '@hono/zod-openapi';
export const InlineSchema = z.object({ ... }); // not allowed in barrel
```
